This paper deals with community detection in networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on multilayer networks, which are networks with multiple layers of connections between nodes. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the analysis of social and information networks. The paper also involves statistical inference and machine learning techniques, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.SD (Machine Learning) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper's focus on community detection and network organization also falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
